Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *AI Engineer* position with *Robert Half*. I bring over three years of professional experience designing and delivering AI-driven products — spanning LLM integration, prompt engineering, multi-agent orchestration, and generative model fine-tuning — along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade AI systems that directly reflect the depth of LLM integration, scalable deployment, and cross-functional collaboration this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, applying prompt engineering and routing optimizations that maximized KV-cache hit rate — reducing end-to-end LLM latency by 60% and API costs by 50%. I also developed an MCP AI interaction layer integrating LLM features across 1,000+ platform endpoints, translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls for scalable, reliable automated customer actions. To keep these AI-driven products production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using LangFuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, and conducted code reviews and performance monitoring to maintain quality over time. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I built an internal support chatbot integrating LLM features via LangChain and RAG with a PostgreSQL vector database — reducing ticket resolution time by 20% — and designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Python, taking it from prototyping to production rollout across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO. Together, these roles have prepared me to design, integrate, and scale AI-driven solutions end-to-end, directly contributing to Robert Half's core engineering responsibilities.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in generative models, model optimization, and technical communication — skills that align directly with Robert Half's values of Innovation and Commitment to Success. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on generative models — StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion — leveraging PyTorch, CUDA, and LoRA fine-tuning on Pace University's HPC cluster. I managed the full model development lifecycle, from training runs to model optimization using vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face, ensuring secure and efficient model serving in production environments. Beyond building these systems, I led workshops on AI Agents with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for 50+ students — translating complex AI concepts into actionable technical guidance, mirroring the collaboration and communication abilities Robert Half values in its engineering teams.

I have always been passionate about innovation in AI and connecting technical solutions to real business outcomes — values that sit at the heart of Robert Half's mission to be the world's leading specialized talent solutions firm. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration — I look forward to connecting!

